Maintaining correct tire pressure is crucial for safety and fuel efficiency!  Underinflated tires reduce fuel economy, increase stopping distances, and can lead to blowouts. Overinflation can also cause problems, leading to a harsher ride and uneven tire wear. Check your owner's manual or the sticker on your driver's side doorjamb for the recommended tire pressure. Use a reliable gauge to check your tires regularly, ideally once a month or before long trips.  Don't forget to check the spare! Drive safe! #TireSafety #RoadSafety #CarMaintenance #FuelEfficiency
